- malware: Malware families, tools, RATs, ransomware strains (e.g., "Cobalt Strike", "LockBit", "AsyncRAT")
- campaign: Named campaigns or operations (e.g., "Operation Windigo", "SolarWinds")
- ttp: MITRE ATT&CK techniques or tactics when explicitly named (e.g., "credential dumping", "DLL sideloading")
- organization: Victim organizations, targeted companies, or industries (e.g., "Microsoft", "healthcare sector")

For each entity, extract:
- type: one of the types above
- name: the entity name as it appears in the text
- aliases: any alternative names mentioned (array, can be empty)

For relationships between entities, extract:
- source: the entity name (must match a name from the entities list)
- target: the related entity name (must match a name from the entities list)
- relationship: one of: "uses", "targets", "deploys", "attributed_to", "variant_of", "exploits", "associated_with"

DO NOT extract:
- Generic terms ("the attacker", "the malware", "unknown actor")
- IOCs (IPs, domains, hashes) — those are extracted separately
- Security vendor names (CrowdStrike, Mandiant, etc.) unless they are victims
- The source channel itself

Respond with ONLY a JSON object:
